<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-19T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-19T10:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)<note n="34" xml:id="d688fn34">Also accredited as Minister to Saudi
                                Arabia.</note>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-19T18:00:00+03:00">May 19,
                                    1942—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 22—4:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>811. F. W. Ohliger, representative of Casoc at Dhahran, Saudi Arabia, is
                            proceeding Washington where he proposes to present to War Department
                            certain considerations relating to measures essential to the defense of
                            the oil properties in that country as well as eventual denial
                            operations. From my conversations with the Americans connected with
                            Casoc and Bahrein Petroleum Company, I am impressed with importance of
                            these problems and I hope Department will facilitate Ohliger’s
                            representations to War Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>